@Taylor Dent, 
Cooking pizza with cast iron is epic. When using cast iron you usually want to use a dutch oven, that is have a lid that can absorb heat as well.
my suggestion is to heat the cast iron first and with a peel drop the pizza into the pan so you can use the heat of the pan to do the cooking, and, make it well covered with a lid of some sort, any pan / lid is better than foil and it should work well.

&#8220;In a large pot eat the coconut oil or vegan butter over medium&#8221;
This was the most difficult part of the recipe for me. It took me ages to find a medium willing to come to my kitchen and sit on the floor while I ate coconut oil above her. 🙂
Seriously though. Thank you so much for the recipe &#8211; great to experience dal makhani again (after having gone vegan).

Made the sauce to go with some pre-made pakoras&#8230;
it is truly *amazing* !!!
I was skeptical with no frying, but seriously this is awesome, thank you!
